cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with learning representations of 3D scenes from multiple sensory modalities, which involves visual perception. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions embodied agents and the development of a Multisensory Embodied 3D-Scene Environment (MESE). 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a novel method for learning latent representations of 3D scenes. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with the inference of representations of the physical world, which is a fundamental problem in AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a neural network model for learning multisensory representations.
